One of these posts will get moved to the quest forum and get a lot less feedback.  Sorry but you evidently missed the point of my post or I wasn't clear enough.  You can reach reach reach to the point that you could call a MM raid a faction &quot;quest&quot; for ring of scale.  Well, move all MM posts to the quest forum.  My question had *less* to do with the quest itself than it had to do with taking down a boss mob.  Ergo, IMO, it should not have been moved where it would get less exposure from people who may have been able to comment on it or you defeat the purpose of a discussion forum.  In fact, I consciously made the decision to post in General specifically for that reason.  I'm not advocating chaos but I'm saying that is a classic example of how moderation backfires.<br>
<br>
I don't know where you came up with the notion that I thought certain forums were exclusive or restricted by who may participate.  <br>
<br>
In economics terms they're called positive and negative externalities.  In laymen's terms people often use the phrase &quot;Don't throw the baby out with the bath water&quot;.  Organization is fine, I'm merely pointing out the potential dangers and giving an example.  Would you prefer a less readable forum with better information and discussion?  Or would you prefer a more readable forum with worse information and less discussion?  <br>
